               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-304-person2208">
                  JOHN 
                  NEWTON
               <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2208" type="surname" value="NEWTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2208" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2208" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the morning of the 2nd of August I saw Smith coming out of Chapel-street, into Lamb's Conduit-street, drawing a spring-cart; I saw him again in Brunswick-square, and Froom with him - Smith then gave up the shafts, and Froom drew it some distance; then Smith took it, till they came to Gower-street, and there they left it; I stopped Smith in Gower-street North, and said he must come with me - he said it was all nonsense; I took Froom on the 3rd of August, in a stable - I was behind a door, and heard him say,"We shall go down to the office to-morrow, and hear more about it."</p>
               <p>Smith. I was hired to draw it to the corner of Tottenham court-road. Witness. He did not say so at the time; he did at the office.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-304-person2209">
                  GEORGE 
                  WISEMAN
               <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2209" type="surname" value="WISEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2209" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-304-person2209" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Queen's Head-court, Grays' Inn-lane. The cart is mine; on the Monday night I had left it safe in <placeName id="t18310908-304-crimeloc1563">Cockpit-yard</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-304-crimeloc1563" type="placeName" value="Cockpit-yard"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-304-crimeloc1563" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-304-off1561 t18310908-304-crimeloc1563"></join>, which is no thoroughfare; it had stood there for two years - I missed it the next morning, between five and six o'clock, and saw it again between seven and eight; it is worth 15l. - my name is on it.</p>
               <p>SMITH - <rs id="t18310908-304-verdict1564" type="verdictDescription">
